# trading-data-flow

## Core Trading Data Flow Components

1. Trade Signal Processing Pipeline
- Ingests TradingView webhook signals 
- Validates trade parameters and risk limits
- Routes signals to appropriate exchange APIs
- Handles paper/live trade execution modes
- Maintains atomic transaction guarantees

2. Position & Balance Tracking
- Real-time position state management
- Multi-exchange balance aggregation
- Fee tracking and P&L calculation
- Position sizing enforcement
- Margin requirement validation

3. Performance Analytics Pipeline
- Trade execution log aggregation
- Win/loss ratio calculations
- Drawdown monitoring
- Fee impact analysis
- Strategy performance metrics

4. Bot Execution Queue
- Prioritized trade execution scheduling
- Multi-bot state coordination
- Exchange rate limiting compliance
- Execution confirmation tracking
- Error recovery workflows

5. Data Persistence Flows
- Trade history archival
- Performance metric aggregation
- Bot state synchronization
- Balance snapshot management
- Audit log maintenance

Key Integration Points:
- TradingView -> Webhook Processor -> Exchange APIs
- Bot Manager -> Execution Queue -> Trade Router
- Performance Tracker -> Analytics Engine -> Reports
- Balance Monitor -> Position Manager -> Risk Engine

Critical Data Paths:
/tradingview-webhook -> /bot-executor-queue -> /exchange-apis
/bot-activity -> /performance-analytics -> /bot-report
/market-data -> /position-manager -> /risk-validator

